	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Is there any NES emulator reusable library?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm wondering if there are NES emulators that instead of being a full running application, are reusable libraries you can interface with to make a working emulator. This way you can add specific functionality to the emulation.
<br />Because the NES emulation should always be the same, working exactly (or as close as it can get) to the NES's original way of working.
<br />So do you know any? if there's none I'm gonna build it.
<br />
<br />My idea is that this library has a class you can instantiate and get a full virtual NES running, it should be 100% platform independent, and also implementation independent, meaning it wouldn't output any sound, music or graphics, but have callbacks that you can plug in to implement those outputs.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


